{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"db2cbf17-644e-42da-8820-5fc20c6453c4","content":"The template has a solid foundation but has a few issues that should be addressed before publishing:\n\n**Missing/Recommended fields:**\n1. **`$schema`** — Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for tooling/validation support.\n2. **`description`** — No description field. NuGet discoverability will suffer without one.\n3. **`groupIdentity`** — Recommended for versioning/grouping templates on NuGet (e.g., `\"groupIdentity\": \"MyCompany.WebApi.CSharp\"`).\n\n**Functional issue:**\n4. **`Framework` symbol missing `replaces`** — The parameter won't substitute into project files without `\"replaces\": \"net9.0\"` (or equivalent). Users can select a framework but it won't actually change the `<TargetFramework>` in the generated `.csproj`.\n\n**Verdict:** Not ready yet. At minimum, fix #4 (broken functionality) and add #2 (description) before publishing.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"67345574-98b8-4c46-9b4d-af4b2a6db8ef","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check the required and recommended fields according to the .NET template engine specification.\n\nRequired fields for a valid template.json:\n- `$schema` - Missing! Should reference the template schema\n- `author` - ✅ Present\n- `classifications` - ✅ Present\n- `identity` - ✅ Present\n- `name` - ✅ Present\n- `shortName` - ✅ Present\n- `sourceName` - ✅ Present (optional but good)\n- `tags` - ✅ Present\n\nIssues I see:\n\n\nThe template is missing `$schema` for validation, lacks `groupIdentity` and `precedence` which are recommended for organizing related templates on NuGet, and the `symbols.Framework` choices appear to use an object format when the newer template engine expects an array of objects instead. the template won't actually apply those substitutions to the output. Looking at how templates typically work, I'd expect something like `\"replaces\": \"net9.0\"` to swap values in the project file. Beyond that, there are a few other gaps that would matter for publishing to NuGet: the template needs a `$schema` field for proper validation, a `description` to help users discover it, and ideally a `groupIdentity` to manage versioning. These are the main blockers before this could go live.","outputTokens":942,"requestId":"501D:99ACC:32116E2:36A91EF:69FBE378"},"id":"74fb775c-e258-49c9-b299-c908d02a15b3","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:57:47.919Z","parentId":"fff8eff7-b04a-4bc6-8891-45ab60020659"}
